<br>
 ATTENTION - We now have a new Enchanter in Guild with research at 220 woot. So if need spells researched ck with Klork or Antipants (new ench).<br>
<br>
 I can only do research for Necro / Cleric / Pallys /  Druids / Ranger / Shaman / Beastlords. Other normal caster classes must do own research. I found this out by trying to do a mage spell research ..... sorry Liltrysten.<br>
<br>
 Klork's research skill is at 200 (with a +5 % modifier) -<br>
<br>
 so if you are looking for your high end spells but don't want to waste time getting ur research skill up, ask me to try it.<br>
<br>
 I have printed the spell research info from EQTRADERS.com and know what is required for the spells.<br>
<br>
 YOU have to tell me what class/spell you want researched - and I can tell you what u need to find. OR you can look up the info yourself - get components - then give to me for combine.<br>
<br>
 The new zone VEKSAR under Lake of Ill Omen seems to be dropping lots of high end research items. Contact ALL your EQ friends and have them save anything they get there for you (or me hehe). I have some mage stuff / some ench stuff / some wizzy stuff / and some necro - I can use all the items that say &quot;tradeskill&quot; ..... anything looted that someone doesn't want please collect for me. I can either use them for guild spells or use them to trade for items I need later.<br>
<br>
 This will save guild members alot of plat - some of my lvl 60 spells sell in bazaar for 40kpp atm. Being able to research these high end spells will hopefully get the price down for all.<br>
<br>
 If you would rather sell your looted items in the bazaar, I understand, as some of the components are selling for 3 - 4kpp each for these hi end researched spells.<br>
<br>
 Thanks<br>
